cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for detecting out-of-distribution samples in deep neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The method is based on softmax of scaled cosine similarity, which is a technique used in metric learning. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security)
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing)
